<br>
I think it is the Sceptre of the Coldain Ancients that the Queen in CC always drops.<br>
<br>
Btw, the quest is VERY buggy, I am attempting it again soon. I've read strategies to doing the quest and guiding the Broodmother (the buggy part) and still it can go buggy. GM's will not help you here, I've tried. People say that sometimes the BM becomes a pet of a random mob. Well apparently that is because when you give the BM the 'controling harness' - anything can control her so you must stay close to her and guide her to the fort (camo up) in theory this works in game it didn't for me.<br>
<br>
So if it doesn't work out the first time just collect the ingredients again and try it again, the legs are worth it (roughly equivalent to Planar armor I think).<br>
<br>
Oh and btw, make sure you announce to the zone that you are do the quest and to leave the BM and the named giants at the fort alone.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps<br>
<br>
Strength and Honor<br>
<br>
Tanluas<br>
Warden of Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upaldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Paldor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/12/01 7:24:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5119.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I have Blood Wolf Harness...</span><hr size=1> Kromrif Legs blow away Verm Pants.<br>
